Usage: ./configure [FLAGS]

Compulsory Flags:
	--dset   <dataset_name>		Specify the name of the dataset under experimentation. 
					The dataset <dataset_name> must reside in the dataset folder.	

Preferably Compulsory Flags:
	--label1 <label1>		Specify the label of the first class of the dataset.
					If not specified it takes the label to be neg

	--label2 <label2>		Specify the label of the second class of the dataset.
					If not specified it takes the label to be pos

	--size	 <size>			The number of files in each class of the dataset.
					If not specified it takes the number of files in each class to be 1000.  
	

Optional Flags:
	--stoplist <stopfile> 		Specify the name of the stop file in case you use your own list of stop words. 
					The file <stopfile> must reside in the preprocess_files folder.
					If not specified it uses the default stop file in preprocess_files/stop_word  

	--n <no_folds>			Specify the number of fold validation you want to use. 
					If not specified it takes n to be 10.

	--help				Opens this menu
